00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:20,680
And here is when you are
the point of contact

321
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,680
how do you do that?

322
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:29,700
This is when you're invited to
give a talk, how do you do that?

323
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:31,700
And--

324
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:35,700
Yeah. It’s very interesting to
read these early documents to

325
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:40,800
look at how early on g0v contributors
think about these issues.

326
00:23:44,940 --> 00:23:49,740
And these issues also
persists in the community.

327
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:51,740
People still think about them

328
00:23:51,740 --> 00:23:53,740
and all kinds of different mechanisms

329
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:58,200
are still being evolved, or being changed
