330
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:00,580
There's two examples here

331
00:24:00,580 --> 00:24:05,860
I'd like to provide that actually set up
concrete mechanisms for g0vernance.

332
00:24:06,860 --> 00:24:13,060
The first one is the amendments,
or how to amend the g0v communi--

333
00:24:13,060 --> 00:24:15,060
Sorry, the g0v manifesto.

334
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:20,400
Remember the-- one of the first
ideas we talked about in the g0v manifesto

335
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:23,540
is how g0v describes itself.

336
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:30,140
So what happens if g0v
evolves and the description

337
00:24:30,140 --> 00:24:34,460
when it was founded no longer fits
the current situation?

338
00:24:34,460 --> 00:24:40,640
It's sort of like, how do we
amend our constitution when--

339
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:43,220
things have changed, when time has passed,

340
00:24:43,220 --> 00:24:48,320
when the situation
is very different from before.

341
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:55,920
So, in October 20th, 2019
some g0v-ers actually came up

342
00:24:55,920 --> 00:25:00,260
with a procedure of how to amend
our manifesto.

343
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:07,220
The central idea is that anyone
can propose an amendment to the manifesto.

344
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:11,260
And there are also
some conditions regarding

345
00:25:11,260 --> 00:25:13,660
how do you propose an amendment.

346
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:18,700
It has to be proposed
in the big hack-a-thons

347
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:22,140
that g0v community hosts
every two months.

348
00:25:22,140 --> 00:25:26,140
It has to have a host
of this proposal, meaning that

349
00:25:26,140 --> 00:25:30,140
one person has to be the point of contact
of this proposal.

350
00:25:31,180 --> 00:25:35,420
And it has to have
open documents that anyone can read

351
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:39,420
about the proposal and
how it's being discussed in--

352
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:41,620
in the hack-a-thon
and also in follow-up meetings.

353
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:44,500
And once the proposal is finalized,

354
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:48,500
it has to have a public review period
of two weeks.

355
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:54,360
And it has to the link of the proposal
has to be posted in g0v's Slack

356
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:57,000
for as many people to see as possible.

357
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:03,000
And if there's no opposing opinions
in two weeks,

358
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:09,080
then the proposal is adopted
and it becomes sort of the new manifesto.

359
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:16,120
And if there are opposing ideas,
or opinions, then we would resolve

360
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:21,840
to general discussion in the general channel
of g0v's Slack.

361
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:27,750
So this kind of
procedure is very important

362
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:33,840
because it lists out exact steps
of the g0vernance.

363
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:37,840
It's not vague ideas or
vague, abstract concept.

364
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:41,840
It's actually-- it's actually
something that you can follow

365
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:44,650
and go through and, you know,
this is a checklist,

366
00:26:44,650 --> 00:26:49,840
so it's very easy to see where
each of these proposals

367
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:56,120
is in terms of their progress.

368
00:26:56,120 --> 00:27:03,490
So this is actually the final version
that has been proposed on October 20th

369
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:08,040
and it was passed
two weeks later on November 4th.

370
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:13,300
It amends the original manifesto
into its current form.

371
00:27:15,780 --> 00:27:21,980
So, this document also provides
some history of the original manifesto

372
00:27:21,980 --> 00:27:25,980
and the changes underneath this.

373
00:27:25,980 --> 00:27:29,980
And a log of all kinds of discussions
that happened during the hack-a-thon

374
00:27:29,980 --> 00:27:32,180
and also during follow-up meetings.

375
00:27:36,660 --> 00:27:41,460
One of the interesting points that
happened during this discussion

376
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:44,220
is the phrase, 'liquid democracy'.

377
00:27:44,860 --> 00:27:47,260
When g0v was first founded

378
00:27:47,260 --> 00:27:51,260
the idea of liquid democracy actually
excites a lot of people.

379
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:57,520
And it was in the mani-- it was
put inside the original manifesto.

380
00:27:58,180 --> 00:28:04,180
But over time, we realized
the difficulties of the liquid democracy

381
00:28:04,180 --> 00:28:08,380
and in the current form of the manifesto,
this term no longer exists.

382
00:28:10,860 --> 00:28:16,500
The other interesting part is about
freedom of speech, or freedom of expression.

383
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:19,100
And there are-- there are talks about

384
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:23,100
if freedom of expression is
actually the best way,

385
00:28:23,100 --> 00:28:27,620
or the best phrase to describe
what we support fundamentally.

386
00:28:29,260 --> 00:28:33,220
But then, the term actually--

387
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:36,260
well, after a period of
discussion, the term actually--

388
00:28:36,260 --> 00:28:38,260
the people have decided
that this term actually

389
00:28:38,260 --> 00:28:42,260
is still the best way to
describe what we think here,

390
00:28:42,260 --> 00:28:48,760
so it was put--
it was kept unchanged.

391
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:54,760
So, this is a very good example
for me to see,

392
00:28:54,760 --> 00:29:02,190
while g0v has fundamental ideas as foundations
or infrastructure as the community,

393
00:29:02,190 --> 00:29:05,080
it's also very adaptable
and it's also very open

394
00:29:05,100 --> 00:29:09,780
and transparent when people
when people propose change.

395
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:15,960
Open discussions are facilitated
and different ideas are considered.

396
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:29,360
This sort of for me, in a way,
manifests g0v's own beliefs in itself,

397
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:33,410
which is very interesting
and very good to me, I think.

398
00:29:34,940 --> 00:29:39,980
The second example is
how the g0v community

399
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:43,080
governs its social media platforms.

400
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:47,840
And as you might know,
g0v has a official--

401
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:50,660
Facebook account, Facebook page, actually.

402
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:55,360
So, the question,
the concrete question is

403
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:59,880
who gets to post what
on g0v's Facebook page?

404
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:08,060
So, this has been very vague
for some time.

405
00:30:08,460 --> 00:30:13,260
And some time last year,
some g0v-ers, including myself,

406
00:30:13,260 --> 00:30:17,260
decided to come together
and discuss if we can set up

407
00:30:17,260 --> 00:30:21,200
a concrete checklist-style mechanism

408
00:30:22,100 --> 00:30:29,050
for all g0v contributors to follow

409
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:34,200
and while not make
the g0v Facebook page

410
00:30:36,100 --> 00:30:40,100
the tool for a minority of
the g0v contributor,

411
00:30:40,100 --> 00:30:44,740
but actually anyone can propose a post
to be posted.

412
00:30:44,740 --> 00:30:50,840
So, this is the final mechanism
that was discussed and decided.

413
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:57,840
And we have decided that
there will be a group of reviewers

414
00:30:57,840 --> 00:31:05,080
that reviews every post that's been
proposed to be posted.

415
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:07,840
And fundamentally, what's important

416
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:12,040
is that all the proposals
and all the discussions

417
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:14,040
has to take place
in public spaces.

418
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:17,500
In public channels on Slack,

419
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:21,740
or in public shared documents
like Google Docs or HackMD,

420
00:31:21,740 --> 00:31:24,040
so that it remains transparent.

421
00:31:25,940 --> 00:31:29,940
We have also decided--

422
00:31:29,940 --> 00:31:34,860
The g0vernance mechanism or model
of the reviewer group--

423
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:36,860
Who gets to be a reviewer?

424
00:31:36,860 --> 00:31:42,400
Anyone can say that he or she
or they want to be a reviewer.

425
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:49,020
And if two people agree, they can join
the reviewer group and become a reviewer.

426
00:31:52,460 --> 00:31:58,180
We have also discussed the review period,

427
00:31:58,180 --> 00:32:05,240
meaning how long does a post
have to be reviewed before it's posted?

428
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:10,760
So, this is a very concrete and

429
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:15,620
and something that could be practiced
in reality.

430
00:32:15,620 --> 00:32:22,820
And this mechanism has actually been
heavily enforced

431
00:32:22,820 --> 00:32:24,820
during the past couple of months

432
00:32:24,820 --> 00:32:26,820
because right now, the g0v community

433
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:31,180
is preparing for its summit
at the end of this year

434
00:32:31,180 --> 00:32:35,380
and because of the promotional
needs of the summit,

435
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:43,740
there were a lot of posts being proposed
to the reviewers to be posted,

436
00:32:43,740 --> 00:32:45,740
And the workload spiked

437
00:32:48,420 --> 00:32:52,540
and produced a lot of workload
for the reviewers.

438
00:32:52,540 --> 00:32:56,940
And that was a challenge
for this mechanism.

439
00:32:56,940 --> 00:33:01,970
And perhaps there will be a discussion of
how to make it more efficient in the future.

440
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:06,050
But the important thing is--
the important thing is all this--

441
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:11,260
all these discussions are transparent
and open to anyone to see and participate.

442
00:33:11,260 --> 00:33:18,460
So, that it doesn't become
closed off and abused by some people,

443
00:33:18,460 --> 00:33:20,460
rather the other.

